---
import varaha_avatar from "../assets/varaha-avatar.jpg";
---

<body
    class="font-sans leading-relaxed mx-auto max-w-5xl p-10 bg-gray-50 text-gray-900"
>
    <header class="border-b border-wiki-border pb-3 mb-5 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Varaha Labs</h1>
        <p>Fostering Open Source Development in Indian Academia</p>
    </header>
    <nav class="mb-8 text-center">
        <a href="#about" class="text-wiki-link hover:underline mx-4">About</a>
        <a href="#projects" class="text-wiki-link hover:underline mx-4"
            >Projects</a
        >
        <a href="#contribute" class="text-wiki-link hover:underline mx-4"
            >Contribute</a
        >
        <a href="#contact" class="text-wiki-link hover:underline mx-4"
            >Contact</a
        >
    </nav>
    <div class="bg-white border border-wiki-border p-8 mt-5">
        <img
            src={varaha_avatar.src}
            alt="Varaha Avatar - Our Inspiration"
            class="max-w-[300px] mx-auto my-5 border border-wiki-border p-2 bg-white"
        />
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
            Our name is inspired by Varaha Avatar, symbolizing the preservation
            and upliftment of knowledge, much like our mission to elevate open
            source development in India.
        </p>

        <h2
            id="about"
            class="text-xl font-bold border-b border-wiki-border pb-2 mt-10"
        >
            About Us
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
            Varaha Labs is an open source initiative dedicated to creating and
            maintaining large-scale projects that can be effectively solve large
            scale problems across India. Our mission is to bridge the gap
            between academic learning and practical software development through
            open source collaboration.
        </p>

        <h2
            id="projects"
            class="text-xl font-bold border-b border-wiki-border pb-2 mt-10"
        >
            Current Projects
        </h2>
        <ul class="list-none p-0 mt-4">
            <li class="mb-6 pl-6 border-l-3 border-wiki-border">
                <strong>Shell-Pa</strong>
                <p>Your sherpa for linux shell, powered by local llms.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="mb-6 pl-6 border-l-3 border-wiki-border">
                <strong>Durga Puja Pandel Hopper</strong>
                <p>Your one stop sidekick to Durga Puja 2025.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2
            id="contribute"
            class="text-xl font-bold border-b border-wiki-border pb-2 mt-10"
        >
            How to Contribute
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
            We welcome contributions from students, faculty, and developers
            across India and beyond:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-8 mt-2">
            <li>Visit our GitHub repository</li>
            <li>Join our WhatsApp community</li>
            <li>Participate in our monthly meetups</li>
            <li>Mentor student developers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2
            id="contact"
            class="text-xl font-bold border-b border-wiki-border pb-2 mt-10"
        >
            Contact Us
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4">Get in touch with the Varaha Labs community:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-8 mt-2">
            <li>
                GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/varaha-labs"
                    >github.com/varaha-labs</a
                >
            </li>
            <!-- <li>
                    Email: <a href="mailto:community@varahalabs.org"
                        >community@varahalabs.org</a
                    >
                </li> -->
            <li>Email: to_be_updated</li>
            <li>WhatsApp Community: to_be_updated</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <footer class="mt-8 text-center">
        <p>
            &copy; 2025 Varaha Labs. Open Source Initiative. All code released
            under MIT License.
        </p>
    </footer>
</body>
